snippet.textDisplay: The way he composes music has always baffled me. First Love was when I realised he is an actual prodigy, a freaking genius. The way that song paints a picture takes your breath away. You live through the memories, you live through the emotion and you don't even notice how the instrumental escalates how the piano plays faster and more agressively until the tempo slows down again in the end. Same with this song. The shift in the second part of the song showcases so well that his shadow and his persona are one but not the same. And there are so many symboliv elements in the video, this is just amazing.
